Formatter-HTML-Preformatted version 0.95
========================================

This module conforms to the Formatter API Specification, version
0.95. The specification itself can be found in the Formatter module on
CPAN. 

This formatter is very simple, it only takes a block of plain text,
possibly with some URIs in line, slaps pre-elements around it and
makes hyperlinks of the URIs.

INSTALLATION

To install this module use the cpan or cpanplus tools or type the
following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module depends heavily on URI::Find::Simple to do its hard work.

SUBVERSION REPOSITORY 

This module is currently maintained in a Subversion repository. The
trunk can be checked out anonymously using e.g.:

  svn checkout http://svn.kjernsmo.net/Formatter-HTML-Preformatted/trunk Formatter-HTML-Preformatted


